My boyfriend and I came to Tutto for the first time on Valentine's Day. We had bought a Groupon a month before & made reservations soon after. I must say, the food was good but the service- not so much. My boyfriend was excited to try the pizza, but when we ordered it our waiter explained that "it was too busy to make pizza". After looking around at the calm restaurant, we decided to order steaks. We were a little upset that the Groupon was not accepted, considering that there was nothing said about not being able to use it on Valentine's Day. When I complained to the manager, he told me that if I looked at the menu I would see that they didn't accept the Groupon today. I told him that I didn't buy it off the menu... I bought it online- where it said absolutely nothing about the exception. He responded with "Well, we don't accept it so just return the Groupon". I was a little put off by that but tried to ignore the fact that we found this out after buying steaks and wine. After that, our experience at Tutto started to get worse and worse. Soon after receiving our check and signing it, our waiter came to the table and picked it up. It was a little rude considering that A) we were still at the table, and B) he never said thank you or have a good night. To top that off, our waiter came back to our table while we were still sitting there and lifted our To-go bag, trying to find our cash tip. After not seeing it (I was going to leave the cash on the table once we left), he dropped our bag on the table and made an angry gesture and then walked away. My boyfriend and I looked at each other & were so shocked by what had just happened.

Tutto's is the Italian restaurant on Congress at the south end of the loop with an old train box car hosting the main dinning room. The food at Tutto's was nice and authentic. Don't expect a high end experience and I wouldn't recommend this spot for a date but it is a good meal. Expect a loud happy hour crowd on Fridays and some nights during the week. This does happen to be a fun drinks spot after work for a number of financial district workers before they jump on the Blue Line (the subway line entrance is just a few steps down Congress).

I was pretty happy with my Salmon Salad,  the fish was perfect, not to dry and not to soft, even the salad and the dressing was very good. Service are friendly and fast... I think it was also a bit earlier then the local people are taking them dinner!  I enjoyed the train restaurant !!!

This is quite possibly the worst Italian food I've had in the last ten years and was WAY overpriced!  I went there with a Groupon and would have been much happier at a noodles and company chain!. Felt like a bad Tony Soprano wanna be diner.  On a positive note the service was very good and very attractive. Here's what I ordered...  House salad - mostly iceberg lettuce with a very average dressing. Was acceptable.  Bread with olive oil - the oil was god awful. Tasted butter and stale. One bite and I was done. Was so sad as usually my favorite!  Mediterranean chicken pasta - sauce was bland and chicken was dry... Was by far best part of meal.  Side of broccoli - cooked well but covered with an uninspiring blend of garlic, butter and water.

The lasagna was some sort of sick joke.  It was pure ricotta cheese between the noodles. A weak meat sauce was poured around the plate.  The worst part of it was that the thing was totally cold.  I don't understand how this could be sold by well meaning people.
